t: A Song or Psalm of David.
O*p God, my heart is fixed; I will sing and give praise, even with my glory.
Awake,*p psaltery and harp: I myself will awake early.
I*p will praise thee, O Lord,*s among the people: and I will sing praises unto thee among the nations.
For*p thy mercy is great above the heavens: and thy truth reacheth unto the clouds.
Be*p thou exalted, O God, above the heavens: and thy glory above all the earth;
That*p thy beloved may be delivered: save with thy right hand, and answer me.
God*p hath spoken in his holiness; I will rejoice, I will divide Shechem, and mete out the valley of Succoth.
Gilead*p is mine; Manasseh is mine; Ephraim also is the strength of mine head; Judah is my lawgiver;
Moab*p is my washpot; over Edom will I cast out my shoe; over Philistia will I triumph.
Who*p will bring me into the strong city? who will lead me into Edom?
Wilt*p not thou, O God, who hast cast us off? and wilt not thou, O God, go forth with our hosts?
Give*p us help from trouble: for vain is the help of man.
Through*p God we shall do valiantly: for he it is that shall tread down our enemies.
